  "prompt": "How much money per hour do Uber drivers make in Des Moines? What's the most a person can reasonably make per month?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, Uber drivers' earnings can vary widely depending on several factors, including location, hours worked, demand, and individual driving strategies. In Des Moines, Iowa, Uber drivers typically make around $15 to $25 per hour before expenses, but keep in mind that this can fluctuate based on peak hours, surge pricing, and operational costs such as fuel, maintenance, and insurance.\n\nRegarding monthly earnings, if a driver works full-time (around 40 hours per week), they could potentially earn between $2,400 and $4,000 per month before expenses. However, it's important to note that expenses can significantly reduce take-home pay, so actual earnings after costs could be lower.\n\nDrivers who work part-time or during peak times (like weekends and events) may earn less overall. For a more accurate estimation, it would be best to consult local driver forums or platforms where drivers share their recent earnings, as these figures can fluctuate over time and with market conditions.",
